 Mincho" w:cs="MS Mincho" w:hint="eastAsia"/></w:rPr><w:t> </w:t></w:r><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:cs="Calibri"/></w:rPr><w:t>the subfolder Ex9_02 to the chapter folder with the name Ch09.</w:t></w:r><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="MS Mincho" w:eastAsia="MS Mincho" w:hAnsi="MS Mincho" w:cs="MS Mincho" w:hint="eastAsia"/></w:rPr><w:t>  </w:t></w:r><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:cs="Calibri"/></w:rPr><w:t>Note that only source files are included in the code downlo</w:t></w:r><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:cs="Calibri"/></w:rPr><w:t xml:space="preserve">ad; there are no project files. Ideally you should create </w:t></w:r><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="MS Mincho" w:eastAsia="MS Mincho" w:hAnsi="MS Mincho" w:cs="MS Mincho" w:hint="eastAsia"/></w:rPr><w:t> </w:t></w:r><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:cs="Calibri"/></w:rPr><w:t>a project file for each example yourself and create the code files for the example as you progress through the text.</w:t></w:r><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="MS Mincho" w:eastAsia="MS Mincho" w:hAnsi="MS Mincho" w:cs="MS Mincho" w:hint="eastAsia"/></w:rPr><w:t> </w:t></w:r><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:cs="Calibri"/></w:rPr><w:t>Typing in the code will enable you to remember how things work much more effecti</w:t></w:r><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:cs="Calibri"/></w:rPr><w:t>vely than if you just read the code</w:t></w:r><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="MS Mincho" w:eastAsia="MS Mincho" w:hAnsi="MS Mincho" w:cs="MS Mincho" w:hint="eastAsia"/></w:rPr><w:t> </w:t></w:r><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:cs="Calibri"/></w:rPr><w:t>or use the files from the code download directly.</w:t></w:r><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="MS Mincho" w:eastAsia="MS Mincho" w:hAnsi="MS Mincho" w:cs="MS Mincho" w:hint="eastAsia"/></w:rPr><w:t>  </w:t></w:r><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:cs="Calibri"/></w:rPr><w:t>If you get into difficulty with an example, you should first try to discover why it is not working</w:t></w:r><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="MS Mincho" w:eastAsia="MS Mincho" w:hAnsi="MS Mincho" w:cs="MS Mincho" w:hint="